ient User Guide (German) V21.0 Reflection FTP Client User Guide (German) V21.1 Reflection FTP Scripting (German) V21.1 Reflection FTP Command Reference (German) V21.1 Last Updated Okt 08, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Set the value of the specified ProcScript function to 1 ( TRUE ). set ProcScriptFunction Example: set $fieldcheck Parameters Table 1. Parameters Parameter Data Type Description ProcScriptFunction Literal ProcScript function Return Values Table 2. Values returned in $status Value Meaning <0 set cannot be used with ProcScriptFunction . 0 ProcScriptFunction was successfully reset. Use Allowed in all component types except self-contained Report and Services. Description The set statement resets the value of the ProcScript function ProcScriptFunction to True ( 0 ). It can be used only with functions for which this feature is documented. Example: set $occcheck The following example uses set to change the value of $occcheck to TRUE ( 1 ): operation exec ; set $occcheck to TRUE to enable checking name = $1 retrieve set $occcheck(INVOICE) edit NAME end; exec Copy Related Links reset Reset the value of the specified ProcScript function to 0. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}